 The Hlalamandi community have blockaded the N11 in the early hours this morning, in protest against Columbus Steel. Residents are disgruntled by the lack of job opportunities. N11 Strike Travellers were advised to avoid using Kilo Street. A www.mobserver.co.za journalist visited the scene and reports that the situation has calmed down, and the Police are currently on standby, monitoring the area. Residents are demanding services. Pumaki Rugby at Laerskool Middelburg MTN the best performing network in Middelburg Increase in kidnapping and murder of children in Mpumalanga VIDEO: Vroue steel sambreel by liefdadigheidsfunksie Die gewilde G.L.O.W kom weer na Middelburg Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za